    "The ANI-1xnr model was trained similarly to ANI models within other contexts 18, including materials science 32 and chemistry 66.",
    "We use the ANI descriptors 67, which is a modified form of the Behler and Parinello NN descriptors 12.",
    "ANI-1xnr uses a local cutoff of 5.2 Å for the radial descriptors and 3.5 Å for the angular descriptors.",
    "The model is trained for the elements C, H, N and O, each of which has its own specialized NN-based potential.",
    "The NN architecture for each element and symmetry functions are reported as Supplementary Tables 2 and 3, respectively."
